# BTMux TODO list

## MUX Todos in the /src/ dir

* Rewrite WHO in Lua
* Start breaking up src/ into system subdirs
* Write tests
* Make integration tests not conflict with running games
* CLI'ify netmux
* Crunch mkindx into netmux
* utf8 support
* Replace the `#pragma clang diagnostic ignored "-Wformat-nonliteral"`
  suppressions with `__attribute__((format(printf, N, M)))` on the printf-style
  wrapper functions that are declared in headers and called pervasively:
  `mech_printf`, `send_channel`, `tprintf`, `safe_tprintf_str`, `log_error`,
  `notify_printf`, `raw_broadcast` (mech.notify.c/comsys.c/formatting.c/log.c/
  netcommon.c), and `lua_set_error` (lua.c). Four file-local helpers with no
  external callers (`append_status`, `append_damage`, `append_lbuf`,
  `do_comprintf`) were already converted this way. Doing the rest properly
  means auditing/fixing every call site the compiler flags once the attribute
  goes on the header declarations — likely hundreds combined. Wiring up just
  `notify_printf` already turned up 3 pre-existing bugs in debug.c passing a
  `DbRef` (64-bit `long`) to `%d` instead of `%ld`.

## Lua Todos

* Add `@luastatus` for effective-module inspection,
  inherited attachment visibility, and pre-attachment validation.
* Expand the explicit Lua host API for object lookup, movement, emits, locks,
  timers, and structured command output; avoid growing dependence on
  `mux.command()` running as #1.
* Improve Lua error and reload observability with handler, event/command,
  object, enactor, source location, traceback, and audit-log context.

## BTech Todos in the /btech/ dir

* Maybe: do we need btech/src/mt19937ar.c or is there something else that may suffice for RNG?
* Remove prototype header files
